The paper discusses the optimization of data transfer in wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the allocation of multiple channels to a single user, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of opportunistic spectrum access (OSA) networks, which involves social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates channel bonding considering physical layer constraints, which involves multimedia (cs.MM).
